Tavatron stopped walking and snarled, she sensed it. Someone, or something, 
was coming. She sighed deeply. If she lingered to long on the thought of 
battle she would only over excite herself. Too much adrenaline, that's what 
her friend had said. Whatever that meant.

"I know, but let's go somewhere... quiet. Away from all this." Tavatron 
gestures to the bridge with her paw. "If Liono needs us, he'll call." 
Tavatron looks up at Dinobot, waiting for his decision.
